// useAgentStatus
// Tracks real-time agent status by polling /api/status and listening for WebSocket events.

Status is one of: working, waiting, idle.
Polling interval is configurable (default 2000ms).
WebSocket updates arrive as a "status_changed" CustomEvent on the window.

FUNCTION useAgentStatus(pollInterval) -> AgentStatusState                      EXPORT
  Manages state: agentStatus, agentMessage, agentIsLoading.
  On mount, performs an initial fetch, then sets a repeating poll at pollInterval.
  Also registers a window listener for "status_changed" events for real-time updates.
  On unmount, clears the poll timer and removes the event listener.

---

FUNCTION fetchStatus()
  Fetches /api/status and parses the JSON response.
  IF the response contains a valid status field (working/waiting/idle), updates state with the new status and message.
  IF the response is invalid or the fetch fails, clears the loading flag but preserves the last known status.

---

FUNCTION handleStatusChanged(event)
  Receives a "status_changed" CustomEvent from the window.
  IF the event detail contains a valid status, updates agentStatus, agentMessage, and clears the loading flag.
